"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from either of two places in England called Prestbury, in Cheshire and Gloucestershire. Both placenames are derived from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>burg</i> ‘fortified place’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Prestbury was born in 1345. She married William de Downes in 1376, in Pott Shrigley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1400, in Pott Shrigley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1345–1400":"1345–1400","1351–1385":"1351–1385","1369–1469":"1369–1469","1377–1436":"1377–1436","1379–1430":"1379–1430","1385":"1385","1351":"1351","Abt 1379":"umbes 1379","1436":"1436","1469":"1469","1369":"1369","1379":"1379","1345":"1345","1377 ":"umbes 1377","1400":"1400","1377":"1377","1376":"1376","1430":"1430","Pott Shrigley, Cheshire, England":"Pott Shrigley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norbury, Derbyshire, England":"Norbury, Derbyshire, England","Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, Unit